&lt;div id="thumbnails" class="anchor">&lt;/div>
&lt;span
class="absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 ltr:-left-6 rtl:-right-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none">
&lt;a class="group-hover:text-primary-300 dark:group-hover:text-neutral-700 !no-underline" href="#thumbnails" aria-label="Anchor">#&lt;/a>
&lt;/span>
&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Blowfish was enhanced in order to make it easy to add visual support to your posts. To do so, you just need to place an image file (almost all formats are supported but we recommend &lt;code>.png&lt;/code> or &lt;code>.jpg&lt;/code>) that starts with &lt;code>feature*&lt;/code> inside your article&amp;rsquo;s main directory, as shown in the example below.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">content
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">└── awesome_article
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> ├── index.md
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl"> └── featured.png
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>This will tell Blowfish that this article has a feature image that can be used both as a thumbnail across your website as well as for &lt;a target="_blank" href="https://oembed.com/">oEmbed&lt;/a> cards across social platforms.&lt;/p></description><media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://muhammadfajarb.github.io/docs/thumbnails/featured.svg"/></item><item><title>Thumbnails</title><link>https://muhammadfajarb.github.io/samples/thumbnail_sample/</link><pubDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://muhammadfajarb.github.io/samples/thumbnail_sample/</guid><description>A quick example of how to start using Thumbnails in your artciles.</description></item></channel></rss>